# so getting coords to pass to citipy to get a city name is kinda redundant since
#    we can just pass coords directly into our api call...but, since thats the way
#    yall wanna be i guess we'll have to make something more complicated than i
#    needs to be.
#
# we gotta get random coords, get whatever citipy says it is, check with weatherAPI 
#    to make sure it doesn't return a 404, then put the returned json into a dataframe.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import json
import requests as req
from citipy import citipy
import random
%matplotlib qt5

def get_random_lat():
    return random.uniform(-90,90)

def get_random_lng():
    return random.uniform(-180,180)

def get_city_name(x,y):
    return citipy.nearest_city(x,y).city_name

def get_country_name(x,y):
    return citipy.nearest_city(x,y).country_code

number_of_cities = 10000
index = 1
units = "imperial"

# insert your own api key below:
api_key = 'PASTEYOURKEYHEREPLZ'
api_url = "http://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?"

weather_df = pd.DataFrame({
    "City" : "",
    "Country" : "",
    "Latitude" : "",
    "Longitude" : "",
    "Temperature" : "",
    "Humidity" : "",
    "Pressure" : "",
    "Wind Speed" : "",
    "Cloudiness" : ""
},
    index=[1]
)

# print(str(len(weather_df)))
while len(weather_df) < number_of_cities:
    
    x = get_random_lat()
    y = get_random_lng()
    
    cityname = get_city_name(x,y)
    countryname = get_country_name(x,y)
    
    search_url = api_url + "q=%s,%s&APPID=%s&units=%s" % (cityname, countryname,api_key, units)
    
    print("%s out of %s: %s, %s \n URL: %s\n" % (index, number_of_cities, cityname, countryname, search_url))
    
    weather_data = req.get(search_url).json()
    
    try:
#         print("weather_data["name"] + ", " + weather_data["sys"]["country"] + " : " +
#         str(weather_data["coord"]["lat"]) + ", " + str(weather_data["coord"]["lon"]))

        weather_df.set_value(index,["City"],weather_data["name"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Country"],weather_data["sys"]["country"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Latitude"],weather_data["coord"]["lat"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Longitude"],weather_data["coord"]["lon"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Temperature"],weather_data["main"]["temp"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Humidity"],weather_data["main"]["humidity"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Pressure"],weather_data["main"]["pressure"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Wind Speed"],weather_data["wind"]["speed"])
        weather_df.set_value(index,["Cloudiness"],weather_data["clouds"]["all"])

        print("No 404 Error! Added %s, %s in position %s! \n" 
              % (weather_data["name"], weather_data["sys"]["country"], str(index)))
        
        print("Checking for duplicates...")
        
        length_pre = len(weather_df)
        print(str(len(weather_df)) + " pre LENGTH")
        weather_df.drop_duplicates("City")
        length_post = len(weather_df)
        print(str(len(weather_df)) + " post LENGTH\n")
        if length_pre != length_post:
            print("*** %s, %s already listed, finging another city for position %s :(" 
            % (weather_data["name"], weather_data["sys"]["country"], str(index)))
        else:
            index = len(weather_df) + 1
        print("-----")
#         index = len(weather_df) + 1
#         count = count + 1

    except KeyError:
        print("\nDude is this even a place??? \n")
        print(str(cityname) + ", " + str(countryname) + " (" + str(x) + ", " + str(y) + ") -- " + str(weather_data["cod"]))
        print("Rejecting this city & finding another one \n **********")
    # get_country_name(5.44608654807,153.003581757)
print("\n got all the infos \n")
